60|$|There is nothing, unless, perhaps, the English language, more terrible {{than the}} {{workings}} of an English railway-line. An instant before {{it seemed as though}} we were going to spend all eternity at Framlynghame Admiral, <b>and</b> <b>now</b> <b>I</b> <b>was</b> watching the tail of the train disappear round the curve of the cutting.|$|R
